(2, 1, '2014-07-22 14:32:46', '2014-07-22 14:32:46', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://www.heytes.com/property2/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sample-page', '', '', '2014-07-22 14:32:46', '2014-07-22 14:32:46', '', 0, 'http://www.heytes.com/property2/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(201, 1, '2014-08-08 17:40:08', '2014-08-08 17:40:08', '[BMo_scrollGallery id="4" ]<img class="ngg_displayed_gallery mceItem" src="http://www.heytes.com/property2/nextgen-attach_to_post/preview/id--312" alt="" />\r\n\r\nWeare delighted to bring to the market this detached Period country style 4 bed family home which is conveniently located just off the N11. Historically the property served as a coach house and hostelry for those travelling between Wicklow and Dublin. In time the property developed into a family home with each owner putting their mark on it. The property oozes charm and tradition with some lovely old world features throughout the property. Although in need of some modernisation, the current owners of the last 15 years have made some significant unseen improvements. The White House is situated on c. 1.5 acres of mature, rambling gardens with a number of out houses. Accommodation briefly comprises of entrance hall, games room / conservatory, 3 reception rooms, living room, kitchen, 4 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms. The property is located just off the N11 which connects to all major transport links and is only a 10 minute drive to Bray Main Street which has a large array of Shops, Restaurants, bars and other recreational facilities and amenities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Features</strong>\r\nHouse on c. 1.5 Acres\r\nTraditional country home with original features\r\nMature gardens\r\nClose proximity to the N11\r\nMains Water &amp; Septic Tank, OFCH\r\nAlarmed and CCTV\r\nBER Details\r\n\r\nBER: F\r\nBER No. 105785232\r\nEnergy Performance Indicator: 405.59 kWh/m/yr\r\n<strong>Accommodation\r\n</strong>Rear Entrance Hall- 1 X 6.2 + 6.8 X 2.1m. Exposed stone wall, sandstone flag stone flooring, T &amp; G panelled ceiling, Guest WC with WC, WHB and tiled floor\r\n\r\nSitting Room- 5.55 x 4m. Original wide plank floor boards, dado rail, picture rail, coving, open fire with slate hearth and marble surround &amp; Mantle piece\r\n\r\nLounge- 4 x 5.2m.Original wide plank floor boards, coving, dado rail, picture rail, Bay window, Open fire with cast iron surround and slate hearth\r\n\r\nKitchen- 4.6 x 3.7m. Tiled floor, Fitted country style kitchen, Tiled Splash Back, plumbed for washing machine and dishwasher, gas range cooker, door to rear patio\r\n\r\nDining Room- 5.45 x 3.2m. original wide plank floor boards, fitted country style display units, arch to kitchen\r\n\r\nStudy- 3.75 x 4m. original wide plank floor boards, ample built in wall shelves, dado rail, picture rail, coving, open fire with cast iron surround and slate hearth, door to rear patio\r\n\r\nLanding- 3.3 x 4m. Mezzanine landing with wooden staircase, carpet\r\n\r\nBedroom 1- 5.7 x 4m. Carpet, shower cubicle with electric shower, WHB, picture rail\r\n\r\nBedroom 2- 3.8 x 4.1m. Carpet, Picture rail\r\n\r\nBedroom 3- 4.14 x 3.7m. Carpet, WHB, picture rail\r\n\r\nBedroom 4- 3.1 x 5m. Carpet, velux window, vaulted ceilings, fire place with tiled surround\r\n\r\nFamily Bathroom- 3.45 x 2.1m. Original wide plank floor boards, WC, WHB, shower cubicle with shower, vaulted panel ceiling\r\nBathroom 2- 1.3 x 4m. Separate toilet and bathroom with original feature toilet and sliding doors, WHB and bath\r\n\r\nGames Room / Conservatory- 8 x 6.3m. Vaulted panel ceiling, double glazed windows throughout to allow for loads of light, double doors to patio\r\n\r\nFront Garden- Graveled entrance, parking for 4+ Cars, also attached to the property is a green house which is in need of some repair\r\n\r\nRear Garden- Mature sprawling gardens, river side setting, vegetable plots, surrounding patio, various out buildings for storage\r\nContact Agent\r\nDirections\r\n\r\nGoing southbound on the N11 our property is located 100m after Kilcroney Church on your left hand side. Keep an eye out for the Fenelon Properties signs.\r\n\r\n<strong>Viewing Details\r\n</strong>By appointment only', '21 The Brurrage, Blessington', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '21-the-burrage-blessington', '', '', '2014-08-09 01:48:30', '2014-08-09 01:48:30', '', 0, 'http://www.heytes.com/property2/?post_type=property&#038;p=201', 0, 'property', '', 0),
